article.headline: N. Arizona 74, E. Washington 71
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Gabe Rogers hit a 3-pointer with 1.8 seconds left in overtime to lift Northern Arizona to a 74-71 win over Eastern Washington on Saturday night. It was the Lumberjacks' third straight overtime game -- the first time in NAU history that has happened. Northern Arizona (13-13, 7-8 Big Sky) lost to Idaho State on Feb. 13, 73-71, in overtime and then topped Portland State 86-85 in double overtime on Thursday. Northern Arizona trailed 69-67 when Rogers hit a 3 with 1:07 left to give the Lumberjacks a one-point lead. The Lumberjacks' DeAngelo Jones hit one of two free throws with 21 seconds left, but Eastern Washington's Glen Dean hit a shot with 10 seconds left to tie it up, setting up Rogers' game-winner. Cameron Jones led NAU with 23 points and Rogers finished with 18. Dean and Brandon Moore each had 13 for Eastern Washington (8-20, 4-10).
